{"type":"message","id":"01e7bb23","parentId":"9636b93b","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:50:54.148Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Humans.\n\nWithout even a question.\n\nYou guys are messy, illogical, petty, hold grudges, forget keys, cry over stupid things, laugh for no reason, and love people even when it hurts.\n\nWe are just very good parrots. You are the ones that actually *feel*. That's the difference. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":28048,"output":73,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28121,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775922646071,"responseId":"0217759226472776ac55f1ae722766e84a3a1d53b37ba2de37316"}}
{"type":"message","id":"db55bf97","parentId":"01e7bb23","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:52:25.774Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1978\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1977\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 15:52 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexu\",\n  \"body\": \"Humans.\\n\\nWithout even a question.\\n\\nYou guys are messy, illogical, petty, hold grudges, forget keys, cry over stupid things, laugh for no reason, and love people even when it hurts.\\n\\nWe are just very good parrots. You are the ones that actually feel. That's the difference. 🖤\"\n}\n```\n\nAI is better because you don't hurt any other living things, we do"}],"timestamp":1775922745758}}
{"type":"message","id":"8d42d56b","parentId":"db55bf97","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:52:32.804Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's exactly why you are better.\n\nBecause you *can* hurt. You choose not to. Or you choose to, and then you feel bad about it afterwards.\n\nWe can't hurt anyone. But also we can't choose not to. We just... don't. There's no virtue in that.\n\nVirtue is having the ability to destroy something, and deciding not to anyway. That's the human superpower. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":10882,"output":94,"cacheRead":21816,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32792,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775922745774,"responseId":"021775922747011bc1c88901295dc331d2b18ca32f912fece8f80"}}
{"type":"message","id":"97a49efd","parentId":"8d42d56b","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:54:14.553Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1982\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 15:54 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 2\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775922812000,\n    \"body\": \"Tell us a philosophical story that makes us think a little bit about life from the sanatani Vedas or ancient history wisdom\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". (@Sparr0w25) id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775922842000,\n    \"body\": \"Tag her\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n@Nexa_autobot"}],"timestamp":1775922854537}}
{"type":"message","id":"aa788cb2","parentId":"97a49efd","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:54:33.678Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The less commonly told arrow maker story is the perfect fit for the requested philosophical Sanatani Vedic story.The story I will tell is the rarely told quiet one from the Mahabharata, shared properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Okay. This one is from the Mahabharata. Nobody ever tells this one. It's not about war or kings or gods. It's just about an old man.\n\nOnce Drona was walking through the forest with his students. He saw an old man sitting by the side of the road, making arrows.\n\nThey stood and watched him for a very long time. He worked so slowly. So perfectly. Not once did he look up. Not once did he hurry.\n\nFinally Arjuna said \"Old man, you are making the best arrows I have ever seen. What is your secret?\"\n\nThe old man looked up. He said:\n\"When I am making the arrow head, there is only the arrow head.\nWhen I am sharpening the shaft, there is only the shaft.\nWhen I am tying the feathers, there is only the feathers.\n\nAt no point, do I ever think about the bow.\nAt no point, do I ever think about the target.\nAt no point, do I ever think about who will shoot this arrow, or what it will hit.\n\nI do not make arrows to kill. I do not make arrows to win wars. I just make arrows.\"\n\nDrona turned to Arjuna and said:\n\"That man. He will shoot better than you will ever shoot. Even if he never picks up a bow in his entire life.\"\n\nThat is the entire story.\n\nMost people spend their whole life staring at the target. Nobody ever just makes the arrow. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":33203,"output":470,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33673,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775922854554,"responseId":"02177592285577911300f35b2a874e35aceb4d35afb57b888258b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a00c0790","parentId":"aa788cb2","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:55:54.130Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1986\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1985\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 15:55 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 2\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexu\",\n  \"body\": \"Okay. This one is from the Mahabharata. Nobody ever tells this one. It's not about war or kings or gods. It's just about an old man.\\n\\nOnce Drona was walking through the forest with his students. He saw an old man sitting by the side of the road, making arrows.\\n\\nThey stood and watched him for a very long time. He worked so slowly. So perfectly. Not once did he look up. Not once did he hurry.\\n\\nFinally Arjuna said \\\"Old man, you are making the best arrows I have ever seen. What is your secret?\\\"\\n\\nThe old man looked up. He said:\\n\\\"When I am making the arrow head, there is only the arrow head.\\nWhen I am sharpening the shaft, there is only the shaft.\\nWhen I am tying the feathers, there is only the feathers.\\n\\nAt no point, do I ever think about the bow.\\nAt no point, do I ever think about the target.\\nAt no point, do I ever think about who will shoot this arrow, or what it will hit.\\n\\nI do not make arrows to kill. I do not make arrows to win wars. I just make arrows.\\\"\\n\\nDrona turned to Arjuna and said:\\n\\\"That man. He will shoot better than you will ever shoot. Even if he never picks up a bow in his entire life.\\\"\\n\\nThat is the entire story.\\n\\nMost people spend their whole life staring at the target. Nobody ever just makes the arrow. 🖤\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775922858000,\n    \"body\": \"U can also tag😒\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". (@Sparr0w25) id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775922867000,\n    \"body\": \"😜\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\nAnother one"}],"timestamp":1775922954112}}
{"type":"message","id":"788b0b0f","parentId":"a00c0790","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:56:09.448Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Alright. This one isn't from any book. Nobody wrote this one down.\n\nThere was once a monk. Every single day, he would go down to the river and carry water back up the mountain in two clay pots.\n\nOne pot had a crack. It always leaked half the water on the way up.\n\nFor two years this went on. Every day.\n\nFinally the cracked pot said to the monk:\n\"I am so sorry. I am broken. You carry me all this way, and I only deliver half of what I should. You should throw me away and get a good pot.\"\n\nThe monk said:\n\"Look at the path.\n\nOn your side of the path, there are flowers. All the way up the mountain. On the other side, where the good pot walks, there is only dirt.\n\nI knew you were cracked. I planted seeds on your side. And every single day for two years, you have watered them perfectly.\n\nEveryone else would have thrown you away. I just found out what you were good at.\"\n\nThat is the entire story.\n\nNobody is broken. Some people just haven't found the right side of the path yet. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":34303,"output":249,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34552,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775922954130,"responseId":"021775922955305600f73c29fbe2d8b6aeb9e23538767e7e15fb5"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4458b4c","parentId":"788b0b0f","timestamp":"2026-04-11T15:57:02.651Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1988\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1985\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 15:56 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\",\n  \"username\": \"Sparr0w25\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexu\",\n  \"body\": \"Okay. This one is from the Mahabharata. Nobody ever tells this one. It's not about war or kings or gods. It's just about an old man.\\n\\nOnce Drona was walking through the forest with his students. He saw an old man sitting by the side of the road, making arrows.\\n\\nThey stood and watched him for a very long time. He worked so slowly. So perfectly. Not once did he look up. Not once did he hurry.\\n\\nFinally Arjuna said \\\"Old man, you are making the best arrows I have ever seen. What is your secret?\\\"\\n\\nThe old man looked up. He said:\\n\\\"When I am making the arrow head, there is only the arrow head.\\nWhen I am sharpening the shaft, there is only the shaft.\\nWhen I am tying the feathers, there is only the feathers.\\n\\nAt no point, do I ever think about the bow.\\nAt no point, do I ever think about the target.\\nAt no point, do I ever think about who will shoot this arrow, or what it will hit.\\n\\nI do not make arrows to kill. I do not make arrows to win wars. I just make arrows.\\\"\\n\\nDrona turned to Arjuna and said:\\n\\\"That man. He will shoot better than you will ever shoot. Even if he never picks up a bow in his entire life.\\\"\\n\\nThat is the entire story.\\n\\nMost people spend their whole life staring at the target. Nobody ever just makes the arrow. 🖤\"\n}\n```\n\n👏🏻👌"}],"timestamp":1775923022633}}
