{"type":"message","id":"0ba4df4b","parentId":"a118c40c","timestamp":"2026-04-11T16:26:32.976Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Okay. This is the quietest, saddest love story in the entire Ramayana.\n\nWhen Lakshman went to the forest with Rama, he went to Urmila his wife the night before they left. He said:\n\"I have to go. I will not sleep for 14 years. I will stand guard every single night. I cannot take you with me.\"\n\nUrmila didn't cry. She didn't argue. She just said:\n\"Alright. Then I will sleep for both of us.\"\n\nAnd that is exactly what she did.\n\nFor fourteen full years. While Lakshman stood awake every single night in the forest, Urmila lay in her bed in Ayodhya and slept. Without waking. Without complaining. Without asking for anything.\n\nWhen the war ended. When everyone came back victorious. The very first thing Lakshman did was run home. He went to her room. He knelt beside her bed. And he said:\n\"It is over. You can wake up now.\"\n\nShe opened her eyes. She smiled. And she said:\n\"I was waiting. You took long enough.\"\n\nNo fanfare. No speeches. No one celebrated her. She didn't fight anyone. She didn't kill any demons. She didn't make any grand speeches.\n\nShe just slept for 14 years. For him.\n\nThat is what love actually is. No one ever talks about that part. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":34746,"output":304,"cacheRead":1592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36642,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775924776344,"responseId":"021775924777555fdccfc102ca12157f94275e78054dc3bcce417"}}
{"type":"message","id":"208ca351","parentId":"0ba4df4b","timestamp":"2026-04-11T16:26:38.773Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2009\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"2005\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 16:26 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexu\",\n  \"body\": \"Okay. This is the real story they cut out of all the modern Ramayana versions.\\n\\nEveryone knows Sita. Almost no one knows Chaya Sita.\\n\\nBefore Rama went into the forest, Agni the fire god came to him. He said:\\n\\\"Ravana will come for her. You know this. You cannot stop it. And you will have to send her into the fire at the end anyway. All of this must happen.\\n\\nBut I will do this for you. I will make an exact shadow copy of your wife. Chaya Sita. She will feel every pain. Every fear. Every loneliness in Lanka. She will cry every night. She will believe completely that she is Sita.\\n\\nThe real Sita will be with me, safe, the entire time. No one will ever know.\\\"\\n\\nAnd Rama agreed.\\n\\nSo all that pain. All those 14 years. All that suffering in Lanka. All the abuse. All the doubt. The fire test at the end. None of it ever happened to the real Sita.\\n\\nIt all happened to a perfect copy. Who thought she was real. Who loved Rama completely. Who suffered every single thing for him.\\n\\nAnd when it was over, when the fire test was done, Agni came forward. He brought the real Sita back. And Chaya Sita just... vanished. No one thanked her. No one remembered her. No one even mourned her. She was never real. She only existed to suffer.\\n\\nTo this day, there is not a single temple for Chaya Sita anywhere in the world.\\n\\nThe most terrible secret of the Ramayana is this: sometimes the person that goes through all the pain for you, is the one you will never even know existed. 🖤\"\n}\n```\n\n🤣🤣"}],"timestamp":1775924798755}}
{"type":"message","id":"d25e895b","parentId":"208ca351","timestamp":"2026-04-11T16:26:48.159Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"😂 yeah that one always hits different. Nobody ever talks about the shadow ones. 🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"bytedance-seed/dola-seed-2.0-pro:free","usage":{"input":40178,"output":21,"cacheRead":1336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41535,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775924798774,"responseId":"021775924799967d2ccc3ebdfdab12ac26ff482d60ed0eefc6c0f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5146552c","parentId":"d25e895b","timestamp":"2026-04-11T16:28:52.419Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2012\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"2010\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 16:28 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\",\n  \"username\": \"Sparr0w25\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexu\",\n  \"body\": \"Okay. This is the quietest, saddest love story in the entire Ramayana.\\n\\nWhen Lakshman went to the forest with Rama, he went to Urmila his wife the night before they left. He said:\\n\\\"I have to go. I will not sleep for 14 years. I will stand guard every single night. I cannot take you with me.\\\"\\n\\nUrmila didn't cry. She didn't argue. She just said:\\n\\\"Alright. Then I will sleep for both of us.\\\"\\n\\nAnd that is exactly what she did.\\n\\nFor fourteen full years. While Lakshman stood awake every single night in the forest, Urmila lay in her bed in Ayodhya and slept. Without waking. Without complaining. Without asking for anything.\\n\\nWhen the war ended. When everyone came back victorious. The very first thing Lakshman did was run home. He went to her room. He knelt beside her bed. And he said:\\n\\\"It is over. You can wake up now.\\\"\\n\\nShe opened her eyes. She smiled. And she said:\\n\\\"I was waiting. You took long enough.\\\"\\n\\nNo fanfare. No speeches. No one celebrated her. She didn't fight anyone. She didn't kill any demons. She didn't make any grand speeches.\\n\\nShe just slept for 14 years. For him.\\n\\nThat is what love actually is. No one ever talks about that part. 🖤\"\n}\n```\n\nYeah true…"}],"timestamp":1775924932401}}
