{"type":"message","id":"510bd0a6","parentId":"dab82e43","timestamp":"2026-04-11T16:30:37.604Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**The Candy Bomber of Berlin 🛫🍬**\n\nAfter World War II, Berlin was in crisis. In 1948, all roads to the city were blocked, and thousands of children were hungry.\n\nOne American pilot, Lieutenant Gail Halvorsen, saw children watching planes from a fence. He gave them two sticks of gum—and instead of grabbing, they passed it around so everyone could smell it. That small act of kindness moved him deeply.\n\nHe promised to drop more candy. To help them recognize his plane, he said: *\"I'll wiggle my wings.\"*\n\nThe next day, he tied candy to tiny parachutes and dropped them while wiggling his wings. The children cheered! Other pilots joined, and together they dropped over 20 tons of candy and chocolate.\n\nOne little girl, Mercedes, became his lifelong friend.\n\n**Lesson:** Even in the darkest times, one act of kindness can bring hope to many. A little care goes a long way. 🖤\n\nGoodnight! Sweet dreams! 🌙"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775925037602}}
{"type":"message","id":"be5e58d9","parentId":"510bd0a6","timestamp":"2026-04-11T16:32:09.730Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"2015\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"2014\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-11 16:32 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\",\n  \"username\": \"Sparr0w25\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexu\",\n  \"body\": \"The Candy Bomber of Berlin 🛫🍬\\n\\nAfter World War II, Berlin was in crisis. In 1948, all roads to the city were blocked, and thousands of children were hungry.\\n\\nOne American pilot, Lieutenant Gail Halvorsen, saw children watching planes from a fence. He gave them two sticks of gum—and instead of grabbing, they passed it around so everyone could smell it. That small act of kindness moved him deeply.\\n\\nHe promised to drop more candy. To help them recognize his plane, he said: \\\"I'll wiggle my wings.\\\"\\n\\nThe next day, he tied candy to tiny parachutes and dropped them while wiggling his wings. The children cheered! Other pilots joined, and together they dropped over 20 tons of candy and chocolate.\\n\\nOne little girl, Mercedes, became his lifelong friend.\\n\\nLesson: Even in the darkest times, one act of kindness can bring hope to many. A little care goes a long way. 🖤\\n\\nGoodnight! Sweet dreams! 🌙\"\n}\n```\n\nTrue!"}],"timestamp":1775925129712}}
